  "prompt": "Does the Tastemaker in Nestl\u00e9 Maggi really contain non-vegetarian substances?",
  "response": "As of my last knowledge update in October 2023, Nestl\u00e9 Maggi's Tastemaker seasoning generally contains vegetarian ingredients. However, it's important to note that formulations can vary by country and product line. There have been concerns in some markets regarding the presence of flavor enhancers, which can sometimes derive from animal sources, but most Maggi products are labeled as vegetarian.\n\nTo ensure that you have the most accurate and up-to-date information, it's best to check the packaging or the official Nestl\u00e9 website for your specific region. If you have dietary restrictions or preferences, always read the ingredient list carefully or contact the manufacturer directly for clarification.",
